<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-5567] With transformations that mutate the topic-partition committing offsets should to refer to the original topic-partition</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-5567</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>
&lt;p&gt;  When a chain of transformations (SMTs) that mutate a record&apos;s topic-partition is applied, then Connect is unable to map the transformed record to its original topic-partition. This affects committing offsets. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; Currently, in order to reproduce the issue one could use the &lt;tt&gt;TimestampRouter&lt;/tt&gt; transformation with a sink connector such as the &lt;tt&gt;FileStreamSinkConnector&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;  In this ticket we&apos;ll address the issue for connectors that don&apos;t manage/commit their offsets themselves. For the connectors that do such management, broader API changes are required to supply the connectors with the necessary information that will allow them to map a transformed record to the original. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
